Rating: 3
I made this since it received a significant amount of positive reviews. This was good but needed help. First I sauteed 2 diced carrots and 2 diced celery with the onion and garlic (more like the beginnings of a bolognese) for extra flavor and extra vegetables. I also added about 2 cups of stock since it would be too chunky with all those veggies. Simmered for 40 minutes with 2 bay leaves (next time I would cut down to one). Pureed it in the food processor and it was good but not great. It was lacking depth. So I threw in a parmesan rind and simmered for 20 more minutes. That made a big difference and gave it what it was missing.

