Like the cook in Nelson, WI, I thought this recipe was pretty terrible too, despite following the instructions exactly. It did, however, give me a decent starting point. I doubled all of the spices, added 3/4 t. of cumin, 1/8 c. + 2 T. of sugar, 1/4 c. of breadcrumbs, 1/4 c. of grated parmesan cheese, and a generous amount of salt and pepper to taste. The cheese and breadcrumbs were necessary to thicken the sauce, which was like water despite simmering for over an hour. In the end, it was the best sauce I ever made (and spicy too - delicious with the Sicilian meatballs on this website). Strange to think it started with a recipe that tasted absolutely awful.

