Rating: 4
Very popular with reviewers, I see, and for good reason. I've been making something very similar for years, and it's great over pasta as-is. But it also lends itself to infinite variations/additions. Browned ground beef or sausage; sauteed mushrooms; finely diced celerey, carrots, and/or bell peppers at the beginning of the cooking process are all pretty obvious additions. Some less obvious additions I've enjoyed: 1) a can or two of white kidney beans, well drained, added near the end of simmering -- with pasta and lots of grated cheese, a good winter vegetarian meal with a glass or two of red wine; 2) a can of solid white tuna (two cans for this much sauce) and some chopped black olives, also added late in the process; 3) plenty of chopped fresh spinach, and several anchovies, both of which will melt away to invisibility but which will leave their flavor. Vary the dried herbs; substitute unsalted butter for the olive oil for a change; top your pasta and red sauce with any grated, chopped, or crumbled cheese of your choice; top with chopped raw green onions. Literally endless options, but remember, the unadulterated version is excellent, too!

